IntersectionTree

public IntersectionTree(FPolygon[] polygons,
                        java.util.BitSet[] sets,
                        java.util.BitSet activated,
                        int maxLevel,
                        double factor)
Creates a new intersection tree with the given polygon set and the bit sets sets. The tree will only be built up to maxIntersections. E.g. maxIntersections=2 intersects only the two sets at most.

Parameters:
polygons -
sets -
maxLevel -
factor - the area factor (area*factor = cardinality)

getByPath

public IntersectionTreeNode getByPath(java.util.BitSet path)
A path is a BitSet with the following properties: The i-th bit corresponds to the i-th group. E.g. to get the intersection node for the sets 0,1 and 3 use the BitSet with the bits {0,1,3} set.
